    "Based on these findings, stakeholders recommended against using the system due to its potential for discriminatory harm.If the initial evaluation showed potential benefits with ways to minimise harm, our review identified accuracy and safety validation as the next crucial step.",
    "The articles included in our review described several practices for accomplishing this, as described in the next section.Ensuring accuracy and safety of AI-enabled systems The included articles suggest that engaging potential realworld stakeholders in the development and testing phases help ensure that the AI-enabled systems performed as intended in actual settings [12,35,36].",
    "For example, one article found that an AI-enabled floor cleaning robot at an airport caused slips and falls and nearly hit a visitor [15], an event that was not predicted during testing prior to deployment.",
    "Specifically, multiple articles mentioned that involving primary stakeholders, such as patients, in evaluating AI outputs helped enhancing the system's accuracy and reliability [36,37].common phase of AI lifecycle (51.11%) (Fig. 5).",
    "Almost half of the included articles (42.22%) used AI-enabled systems as AI-assisted decision-making systems (Table 6 and \"Appendix 3\")."
